author: NEW YORK DAILY NEWS
title: U.S. stock market has one of its strongest weeks of the year
text:
Seth Wenig/AP Stocks have rebounded as Wall Street investors are banking the Federal Reserve will keep interest rates at near-zero levels until at least next year. The U.S. stock market capped one of its strongest weeks of the year with a modest rally Friday.
The S&P 500 rose 0.1% to finish the week up 3.3%, the best increase since December, while the Dow added 34 points to stay above the 17,000-point threshold at 17,085.
GUEST COLUMN: PAY ATTENTION, INVESTORS; STOCK MARKET VOLATILITY SHOULD CONTINUE
Stocks have rebounded as Wall Street investors are banking the Federal Reserve will keep interest rates at near-zero levels until at least next year.
The Dow climbed 3.7% for the week, while the Nasdaq was up 2.6%.
